'''Patreon'''（{{IPAc-en|ˈ|p|eɪ|t|r|i|ɒ|n}}）是一個供內容創建者進行[[群眾募資|群眾募資]]的平台。它讓創作者向[[贊助|贊助者]]以每件作品或定期取得資金<ref>[http://www.californiareport.org/archive/R201407111630/d The California Report.org:  "Creating Patrons of the Arts Through Crowdfunding"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.californiareport.org/archive/R201407111630/d |date=20140714225511 }} July 11–13, 2014.</ref>。該公司總部設於[[舊金山|舊金山]]，由{{le|傑克·康特|Jack Conte}}和開發者山姆·任（{{lang|en|Sam Yam}}）創立<ref>[http://www.patreon.com Patreon.org: Intro] {{Wayback|url=http://www.patreon.com/ |date=20140301150012 }} Accessed 14.7.1014</ref>。Patreon曾被刊登於《[[時代_(雜誌)|時代]]》、《[[告示牌_(雜誌)|告示牌]]》和《[[福布斯|福布斯]]》。

==歷史==
{{le|傑克·康特|Jack Conte}}於2013年5月在尋求以他受歡迎的[[YouTube|YouTube]]影片中維持生活，所以創辦了Patreon<ref name="pbs">{{cite news | url=http://www.pbs.org/mediashift/2013/09/donation-patron-services-help-fans-support-their-favorite-authors/ | title=Donation, Patron Services Help Fans Support Their Favorite Authors | publisher=PBS | date=9 September 2013 | accessdate=1 March 2014 | author=Levitz, Dena | archive-date=2015-05-18 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518171456/http://www.pbs.org/mediashift/2013/09/donation-patron-services-help-fans-support-their-favorite-authors/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。他和山姆·任（{{lang|en|Sam Yam}}）一同開發了一個可以讓贊助者在創作者每創作一件作品，便自動贊助創作者的平台。2013年8月，該公司從一群[[創業投資|創業投資者]]和[[天使投資者|天使投資者]]取得210萬美元資金<ref name="wired">{{cite news | url=http://www.wired.com/business/2013/10/big-idea-patreon/ | title=The Next Big Thing You Missed: ‘Eternal Kickstarter’ Reinvents Indie Art | publisher=Wired | date=22 October 2013 | accessdate=1 March 2014 | author=Tate, Ryan | archive-date=2014-03-30 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140330184916/http://www.wired.com/business/2013/10/big-idea-patreon | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="time">{{cite news | url=http://business.time.com/2013/12/04/business/slide/top-10-exciting-startups/ | title=Top 10 Exciting Startups | publisher=Time | date=4 December 2013 | accessdate=1 March 2014 | author=Luckerson, Victor | archive-date=2014-03-01 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140301040044/http://business.time.com/2013/12/04/business/slide/top-10-exciting-startups/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。2014年6月，公司在一輪A系列投資中取得1500萬元資金<ref name="series A">{{cite web | url=http://techcrunch.com/2014/06/23/patreon-raises-15-million-series-a-revamps-site-to-showcase-artist-content/ | title=Patreon Raises $15 Million Series A, Revamps Site To Focus More On Content | publisher=TechCrunch | date=23 June 2014 | accessdate=26 August 2014 | author=Buhr, Sarah | archive-date=2016-02-15 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160215092610/http://techcrunch.com/2014/06/23/patreon-raises-15-million-series-a-revamps-site-to-showcase-artist-content/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

在公司的首18個月，多達125,000名「贊助人」在Patreon註冊<ref>{{Cite web|title = Amanda Palmer races to $13,000 per release in Patreon crowdfunding|url = http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2015/mar/04/amanda-palmer-patreon-crowdfunding-backers|website = the Guardian|accessdate = 2015-06-11|first = Stuart|last = Dredge|archive-date = 2015-06-09|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150609094524/http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2015/mar/04/amanda-palmer-patreon-crowdfunding-backers|dead-url = no}}</ref>。2014年末，該網站宣佈贊助人每月向創作者贊助超過100萬美元<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.patreon.com/creation?hid=1070951|title = Creators on Patreon Receive Over 1,000,000 per Month From Patrons|date = October 10, 2014|accessdate = June 12, 2015|website = |publisher = |last = |first = |archive-date = 2015-04-04|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150404133954/https://www.patreon.com/creation?hid=1070951|dead-url = no}}</ref>。

2015年3月，由於由[[葛林兄弟|葛林兄弟]]創辦、和Patreon相似的平台[[葛林兄弟|Subbable]]使用的[[亞馬遜公司|亞馬遜公司]]支付系統關閉，所以在此機會下Patreon收購了Subbable。因此，原來使用Subbable的創作者，例如[[CGP_Grey|CGP Grey]]、{{le|德斯坦·桑德林|Destin Sandlin}}的「Smarter Every Day」YouTube頻道及葛林兄弟的[[Crash_Course|Crash Course]]和{{le|SciShow|SciShow}}頻道都改用Patreon<ref>{{cite web|title=Patreon Acquires Subbable, Aligning the YouTube Stars|url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/alexpham/2015/03/16/patreon-acquires-subbable-aligning-youtube-stars/|website=Forbes|accessdate=17 March 2015|archive-date=2016-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160127023454/http://www.forbes.com/sites/alexpham/2015/03/16/patreon-acquires-subbable-aligning-youtube-stars/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2015年10月，網站被[[黑客|黑客]]入侵，約15GB的個人資料和軟件源碼被公開<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hunt|first1=Troy|title=Pwned websites - Patreon|url=https://haveibeenpwned.com/PwnedWebsites#Patreon|website=Have I been pwned?|accessdate=7 October 2015|archive-date=2015-10-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151003211856/https://haveibeenpwned.com/PwnedWebsites#Patreon|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Goodin|first1=Dan|title=Gigabytes of user data from hack of Patreon donations site dumped online|url=http://arstechnica.com/security/2015/10/gigabytes-of-user-data-from-hack-of-patreon-donations-site-dumped-online/|website=ars technica|accessdate=7 October 2015|date=2 October 2015|archive-date=2015-10-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151008042932/http://arstechnica.com/security/2015/10/gigabytes-of-user-data-from-hack-of-patreon-donations-site-dumped-online/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==營運模式==
創作人在Patreon網站設立專頁，而贊助人便可以在專頁設定創作人每次推出作品時贊助金額，贊助人亦可設定每月贊助上限。除此以外，贊助人亦可每月設定贊助特定的金額。與[[Kickstarter|Kickstarter]]不同，創作人無需每件作品重新籌集贊助人<ref name="pbs" />。但和其他群眾募資平台相似，創作人會以獎勵回饋贊助人<ref name="billboard">{{cite news | url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/news/1561353/jack-contes-patreon-anyone-can-be-a-patron-of-the-arts | title=Jack Conte’s Patreon: Anyone Can Be a Patron of the Arts | work=Billboard Biz | date=10 May 2013 | accessdate=1 March 2014 | author=Pham, Alex | location=Los Angeles | archive-date=2016-02-23 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160223065238/http://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/news/1561353/jack-contes-patreon-anyone-can-be-a-patron-of-the-arts | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="mercury">{{cite news | url=http://www.portlandmercury.com/BlogtownPDX/archives/2014/02/07/portland-cartoonist-erika-moen-launches-a-patreon-also-patreon-sounds-pretty-brilliant | title=Portland Cartoonist Erika Moen Launches a Patreon (Also, Patreon Sounds Pretty Brilliant) | work=The Portland Mercury | date=7 February 2014 | accessdate=1 March 2014 | author=Henriksen, Erik | location=Portland, OR | archive-date=2016-03-12 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160312064040/http://www.portlandmercury.com/BlogtownPDX/archives/2014/02/07/portland-cartoonist-erika-moen-launches-a-patreon-also-patreon-sounds-pretty-brilliant | dead-url=no }}</ref>。Patreon在贊助金中取5％[[佣金|佣金]]<ref name="patreonhelpcenter">{{cite web | url=https://patreon.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/204606125-How-do-you-calculate-fees- | title=Patreon Help Center | publisher=Patreon | accessdate=19 August 2015 | archive-date=2015-12-26 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151226040942/https://patreon.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/204606125-How-do-you-calculate-fees- | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

